<s> What you are experimenting is probably (definitely) server push.  </s>
<s> It is a feature of Netscape Navigator that is not part of HTTP 1.x.  </s>
<s> What it does is send a multipart content-type telling the client to replace each part with the next one (thus the page changes).  </s>
<s> Basically, this forces the connection to stay open (though it has nothing to do with persistant connection in HTTP 1.1).  </s>
<s> Servers usually push images (to create some sort of animation), but some also push html text (for the same purpose that you experimented).  </s>
<s> Unfortunately, all servers (including some of Netscape's !) do not implement this consistently and the specs (http://partner.netscape.com/assist/net_sites/pushpull.html) are somewhat unclear.  </s>
<s> Server push has the drawback of forcing the client to keep the connection open by pretending that more data is to come.  </s>
<s> It also requires that the client nkows how to deal with this feature... Explorer and Navigator both implement server push... Hope this helps.  </s>
